**Describe the bug**
I have a retinaface model with multi output layers. How to get those layers?.
![Screenshot from 2019-10-16 18-44-37](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37315746/66916384-499dd180-f045-11e9-9847-c9595b93eefb.png)
Whether I can get those layers in session.run() function?
`auto output_tensors = session.Run(Ort::RunOptions{nullptr}, input_names, &input_tensor_, 1, output_names, 1);`

**Urgency**
I must to implement retinaface and arcface on C++ for my thesis at university.
